vim insertion macros:
(1) insert template, fill in date, copy syntax:
Omo/^functionmf'odd'f"fy$:r COMMENT-TEMPLATEmj/^%kd'j/FuncNameD"fp0Wdf=ix bdwf(D/^% Updated:!!date +Updated:\ \%Y-\%m-\%di% 'f/^% Syntaxf{D"fp0/functiondWf(/varargincw<options>
(2) convert opt from ParseArgs invocation to opt in comment (repeat per opt):
0cf'%		f'r: cf,		f r(Ea) C descrip
(3) convert [] to <auto> (repeat per instance):
/(\[\]) 2s<auto>

% FuncName
%
% Description:	{imperative verb phrase}
%
% Syntax:	{ans = FuncName(args,<options>)}
%
% In:
% 	{arg1}	- {noun phrase}
%	{arg2}	- {noun phrase}
%	<options>:
%		{opt}:		({default}) {noun phrase (or verb phrase?)}
%		{opt}:		(<all>) {noun phrase (or verb phrase?)}
%
% Out:
% 	ans	- {noun phrase}
%
% Notes:
%	notes
%
% Example:
%	example
%
% Updated: yyyy-mm-dd
